description: MOONLIT MANTRAS!!! Experience the magic of MOONLIT MANTRAS!!! Prepare yourself for an unforgettable night filled with sights, sounds, and sensations! Join the exceptional Kirtan Band and other performers for a captivating evening featuring musical meditations, mesmerizing dance, and complimentary cultural food. It is our pleasure to invite you to this EXTRAORDINARY EVENT scheduled for Wednesday, March 27th at 7:00 pm at Rutgers Busch Student Center MPR, and guess what? It's completely FREE OF CHARGE! This is an incredible opportunity that you do not want to miss out on! We're eagerly looking forward to seeing you all there. Step into a world of enchantment under the glow of the moon at "Moonlit Mantra," an immersive cultural experience taking place on March 27th, 2024, from 7:00 pm to 11:00 pm at Busch MPR. Prepare to be transported to a different world as we celebrate the beauty of dance, music, and mantra meditation. As the evening unfolds, immerse yourself in the mesmerizing rhythms and graceful movements of traditional Indian dance performances. Marvel at the intricate footwork and expressive gestures that weave tales of ancient myths and modern expressions, captivating your senses and stirring your soul. Feel the pulsating beat of live music as talented musicians transport you to distant lands with soul-stirring melodies and captivating rhythms. At the heart of "Moonlit Mantra" lies the transformative practice of mantra meditation. Discover the power of sacred sound as experienced guides lead you through meditative chants and mantras, inviting you to connect with your inner self and experience a profound sense of peace and tranquility. And what's a celebration without delicious food? Indulge in a mouthwatering array of Indian food provided free for all attendees. From savory samosas to fragrant Shahi Paneer and decadent desserts such as Gulab Jamun, savor the flavors of India as you mingle with fellow participants and soak in the vibrant atmosphere of the event. Whether you're drawn to the vibrant rhythms of Indian dance, the soulful melodies of live music, or the transformative practice of mantra meditation, "Moonlit Mantra" offers an unforgettable evening of cultural immersion and spiritual exploration. Join us on March 27th for a night of enchantment, connection, and celebration! :)
name: MOONLIT MANTRAS

description: We hope this email finds you well! As Queer individuals, our clothing choices play a significant role in how we express ourselves. Whether it's concert black, administration/interview attire, or teaching outfits, navigating professional wear can be challenging. That's why we're excited to invite you to join us next week for a dynamic exploration of LGBTQIA+ professional attire! During the event, you'll have the opportunity to engage in empowering discussions, gain expert insights, and discover practical tips for navigating workplace attire authentically. Our panelists will showcase go-to outfits, share strategies for determining appropriateness, and review presented outfits. Attendees are encouraged to bring any outfits they'd like to showcase and come prepared with questions. Meet our esteemed panelists:  Tatyana Louis-Jacques, current music educator (They/Them) Brian Yumiguano, current student (She/They)  We're also seeking one more panelist; if you're interested, please reach out to brianyumi11@gmail.com.  When? Wednesday April 3rd, 12:00pm   Where? Art History Room 201, 85 George Street Douglass Campus Don't miss out on this enlightening event!
name: Concert Queer: A Discussion on Professional wear for LGBTQIA+

description: Celebrate the end of the academic year by joining Douglass staff, the Voorhees Choir, and fellow students for the annual Sacred Path Ceremony. One of Douglass' oldest traditions, the Sacred Path ceremony recognizes student achievement and fosters Douglass's unique community. Join your fellow Douglass classmates, alumnae, friends, and family as each class is honored with a symbol representing the different class years. After you receive your charm, head to the ceremonial fires on the sacred path to make a wish!  Students should show their pride by wearing their class year colors (first years wear white, sophomores wear pink, juniors wear red, and seniors wear black). Every student will receive a charm, a token representing her class. All Douglass students, family, faculty, and alumnae are welcome! Refreshments will be provided at Ludwig immediately following the ceremony.  *Students in Knowledge & Power will receive 2 points towards their Douglass event requirements*
name: Sacred Path 2024
